name":"Reygate","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Reigate  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Reigate","meanings":["English: locative name from Reigate (Surrey)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":9,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":34,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":47,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert De Reygate was born about 1281, in Steeton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John De Reygate, was 19 and his mother, Mrs Catherine De Reygate, was 23. He married Elizabeth in 1303, in Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in 1330, in Sherburn, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 50."},"et":{"Abt 1281–1330":"umbes 1281–1330","1281–1330":"1281–1330","1291–Male":"1291–Surnud","1290–1330":"1290–1330","1305–1367":"1305–1367","1307–Male":"1307–Surnud","1309–Male":"1309–Surnud","1263–1314":"1263–1314","1259–1314":"1259–1314","30 Jun 1314":"8. juuli 1314","1330":"1330","1263":"1263","1281":"1281","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","1303":"1303","about 1307":"umbes 1307","1314":"1314","1259":"1259","1367":"1367","abt 1309":"umbes 1309","Abt 1281":"umbes 1281","1309":"1309","1307":"1307","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Steeton, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire West Riding, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sherburn, Yorkshire, England":"Sherburn, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1281–1330":"noin 1281–1330","1281–1330":"1281–1330","1291–Male":"1291–Kuollut","1290–1330":"1290–1330","1305–1367":"1305–1367","1307–Male":"1307–Kuollut","1309–Male":"1309–Kuollut","1263–1314":"1263–1314","1259–1314":"1259–1314","30 Jun 1314":"8. heinäkuuta 1314","1330":"1330","1263":"1263","1281":"1281","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1315":"1315","1303":"1303","about 1307":"noin 1307","1314":"1314","1259":"1259","1367":"1367","abt 1309":"noin 1309","Abt 1281"